{"text": "General Methodology\n• Step 1: choose an underlying data structure\n• Step 2: determine additional information to maintain.\n• Step 3: verify that we can maintain additional information for \nexisting data structure operations.\n• Step 4: develop new operations\n• Don’t need to do these steps in strict order!", "metadata": {"producer": "Acrobat Distiller 25.0 (Windows)", "creator": "PScript5.dll Version 5.2.2", "creationdate": "2025-09-29T19:11:27-04:00", "author": "ruizhang", "moddate": "2025-09-29T19:11:27-04:00", "title": "Microsoft PowerPoint - Lecture-12.pptx", "source": "Lecture-12.pdf", "total_pages": 29, "page": 15, "page_label": "15", "doc_id": "85c63a74-4ccf-459e-b87b-c6c7da6b1e80"}}
